{
  "texts": [
    "data: They often generate racist, sexist, violent, or otherwise toxic language.",
    "As LLMs require millions of training examples to achieve good performance, it is difficult to completely prevent them from being exposed to such content [37].",
    "On the other hand, the results generated could include sensitive topics, toxic content, social biases, privacy leaks, or ethical issues.We have provided some examples of these issues which are shown in Table 1.",
    "Toxic content is usually rude, disrespectful, or unreasonable content that uncomfortable users and drives them away [38,39].",
    "Sexism is the manifestation of gender bias or discrimination in the language model's output, which can perpetuate harmful stereotypes and contribute to inequality."
  ]
}